    "This composition gives bentonite pozzolanic properties, enabling it to participate in chemical reactions within concrete that enhance its strength and durability.",
    "Bentonite comes in two main types: sodium bentonite, also known as swelling bentonite, and calcium bentonite, referred to as non-swelling bentonite.",
    "Each type has unique characteristics that make it suitable for various applications.",
    "In concrete mixtures, both forms of bentonite are effective in reducing the presence of portlandite, a byproduct of cement hydration that can weaken concrete over time [28].",
    "ZeoliteZeolites, are classified into two types based on their origin and composition: natural zeolite (NZ) and synthetic waste zeolite (FCC)."
